@{" About." link "About" 0}

                             @{fg shine}@{bg text} Magnum Opus V3.1a.@{fg text}@{bg back}

                      @{fg shine}Copyright ˋ 1996-98 Richard Lane.@{fg text}
                        @{fg shine}(Released 29, November 1998)@{fg text}

 Do you own Directory Opus Magellan? Fed up wondering exactly what a
particular file is, what produces it, how it can be used, then this is for
you. Magnum Opus contains 435 filetypes together with extensive AmigaGuide
format documentation. In addition a set of replacement toolbar button
images, some icons, and useful buttons are included. 

   Contents... 

  @{" Introduction. " link "Introduction" 0} ---------------------------------- What is Magnum Opus?.
  @{" Requirements. " link "Requirements" 0} ------------------------------ Details of what you need.
  @{" Installation. " link "Installation" 0} ----------------- Installing Magnum Opus on your system.
  @{" Filetypes Overview. " link "Filetypes Overview" 0} ------------- General information about filetypes.
  @{" Filetypes Index. " link "Filetypes_Index" 0} ----- Complete documentation on all of the filetypes.
  @{" Icons. " link "Icons" 0}  -------------------------------- Those little coloured things.
  @{" Buttons banks. " link "Button Banks" 0}  --------------------- Extra buttons for Opus Magellan.
  @{" Screen-back.dopus5. " link "Screen-back.dopus5 module" 0}  ---------------------------- Useful ARexx module. 
  @{" Frequently Asked Questions. " link "FAQ" 0}  -------------------- Further information.
  @{" Hidden Functions. " link "Hidden Functions" 0}  --------- Non-documented features of Opus Magellan.
  @{" Directory Opus Magellan notes. " link "Magellan upgrade" 0}  @{" Pirate Users Note ! " link "PirateOpus" 0}
