   versions 1.0 - 2.2.
 @{b}@{fg shine}ñ@{ub}@{fg text} Added check for disk space
 @{b}@{fg shine}ñ@{ub}@{fg text} New method for installing filetypes implemented, it's now many times
   faster

 @{fg shine}@{bg fill} V1.3. (22 Sept 1997).@{fg text}@{bg back} @{i}Supplied with Magnum Opus 2.2.@{ui}

 @{b}@{fg shine}ñ@{ub}@{fg text} Gave the user in "expert mode" the choice of where to put the filetypes.
 @{b}@{fg shine}ñ@{ub}@{fg text} Added check for existence of Filetypes_ORIGINAL directory.

 @{fg shine}@{bg fill} V1.2. (13 Sept 1997).@{fg text}@{bg back}

 @{b}@{fg shine}ñ@{ub}@{fg text} Corrected run command to show Magnum_Opus.Guide, it now uses complete
   path. I didn't spot this as I personally have Multiview made resident in
   the S:user-startup. 

 @{fg shine}@{bg fill} V1.1. (08 Sept 1997).@{fg text}@{bg back}

 @{b}@{fg shine}ñ@{ub}@{fg text} Removed some unnecessary Makedir commands as "copylib" & "copyfile" can
   do this.
 @{b}@{fg shine}ñ@{ub}@{fg text} It will now install new versions of files even if the old ones are read
   or write protected.
 @{b}@{fg shine}ñ@{ub}@{fg text} Now checks the default tooltype and stack of the Magnum_Opus.Guide.
 @{b}@{fg shine}ñ@{ub}@{fg text} Progress percentage indication re-done

 @{fg shine}@{bg fill} V1.0. (25 June 1997).@{fg text}@{bg back}

 @{b}@{fg shine}ñ@{ub}@{fg text} Initial release supplied with Magnum Opus V2.1.

..
@endnode

@node "Future Plans" "Future Plans"
@{i}Magnum Opus Guide V3.1a @{ui}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text} Future Plans.@{fg text}@{bg back} 

 ñ As I am now connected to the internet one major addition I plan to make
is to create a support Web site for Magnum Opus over the next few weeks.
This should be available from around mid December 1998 as...

                      http://www2.prestel.co.uk/amiga

 ñ There's still more filetypes to come, many new ones are currently being
worked on. There are also various filetypes that I'd like to include in an
update but need some help with, see  Your Help Wanted.  

 ñ If all goes well there will be an interesting development for viewing
various AMOS filetypes.

 ñ Good news for those of you who liked the silly messages in title bar
featured in the earlier versions of the Magnum_Opus.Guide. They're coming
back in the next version, new ones this time. I never thought so many people
would make so much fuss over something so trivial.

 ñ The On-Line help for the filetypes promised back in V2.2 is proving much
harder to implement that I had first thought, I might even have to admit
defeat on this one. 

 ñ I'm looking to change and improve the layout of this Magnum_Opus.Guide.
Various ideas have been suggested and I also have some of my own that I'm
looking to implement. One real possibility is the inclusion of an additional
version of this AmigaGuide that makes use of the extra features available
with Multiview V40.x in Workbench 3.1. This would need to be a separate file
as these extra enhancements do not work in Workbench 3.0. I might even
abandon the AmigaGuide format altogether and convert the documentation into
the more universal @{" HTML." link "HTML, text" 0}

 ñ If there's anything you'd like to see included, changed or updated then
please feel free to get in touch with @{" me." link "Author Information" 0}

..
@endnode

@node "Your help Wanted" "Your help Wanted"
@{i}Magnum Opus Version 3 @{ui}

 @{fg shine}@{bg fill} Your help Wanted.@{fg text}@{bg back}  

 While creating Magnum Opus I have been able to use my own extensive
knowledge of the Amiga, its history and its programs, or obtain reference
material from the Aminet CD's and other sources. However, there are still a
few specific things that I need some help with. If you feel that you are
able to help then please contact @{" me." link "Author Information" 0} Don't just sit there reading this, do
it NOW. 

 @{fg shine}FinalCalc. (Softwood)@{fg text}
 I haven't found anyone who has this program and would be grateful if
someone could supply me with some example files saved out from as many
versions of it as possible. 

 @{fg shine}Various music modules formats.@{fg text}
 Documentation on any of the music module filetypes not covered in this
AmigaGuide. I am especially interested to find out any details on the Future
Composer tracker as I have very little and conflicting information on the
various versions.

 @{fg shine}WordPerfect (Amiga version).@{fg text}
 I'd like to know how well this filetype picks up files produced by any
Amiga version of @{" WordPerfect." link "WordPerfect Filetypes" 0} 

 @{fg shine}Old File crunchers.@{fg text}
 Though I already have most of the old PD/Shareware crunchers there are
still a few that are proving hard to track down. If you have either the
programs and/or documentation of any of the following then Please contact
me.

 @{" ANC Cruncher " link "ANC Cruncher" 0}
  Any version of @{" PowerPacker " link "PowerPacker Filetypes" 0} before V2.1a
 @{" HQC Cruncher " link "HQC Cruncher 2" 0} V1.x and 2.x
 @{" Turbo Squeezer " link "TurboSqueezer 6.1" 0} (any version) 
 @{" StoneCracker " link "StoneCracker Filetypes" 0} any versions not mentioned preferably with the
documentation


 I am always willing to listen to any suggestions or ideas you may have. A
number of these have already been implemented and others will be in the next
version. If there's something that doesn't work as it should or any
inaccuracies in the text then let me know, the more feedback I get then the
better Magnum Opus will become. I'll even call you back so you don't have to
pay for the phone call. Don't forget that your help will be mentioned in the
@{" acknowledgements " link "Acknowledgements" 0} page and you will receive the next version of Magnum Opus
before it is released anywhere else.

..
@endnode

